text:
warning trigger #ednos #babyloss #miscarriage #eatingdisorderrecovery #ana #mia #pleasedieana #metoo *
*
*
*
*

ty @fatgirlfedup for continuing to remind me that i can get healthy & i will do this the right way this time. i don't talk about this a lot but when i was 21 i was 320 lbs and i lost 135lbs in 2 years and kept it off for 12. see people know that part but the part i rarely talk about is the comfort eating due to traumatic life events that lead me to that point. i don't talk about the ephedrine, energy drinks and diet colas i lived on to lose the weight. i'd go for 46-48 hours before i would allow myself half a turkey sandwich or a big green salad. the times i was forced to eat by my family members and then would go purge all the while telling myself i was doing this for my health. not realizing that i had given up the vice of comfort eating for the eating disorder i had invited in the moment i got afraid to put any of that weight back on. i don't talk about the fact that until i got pregnant with my first child (my angel baby nicholas) i was terrified to eat a whole meal and would go through anxiety and guilt if i ate. once pregnant i had to eat for nicholas so i had to face my fears. (he saved my life) unfortunately i miscarried my precious nicholas and i turned to comfort eating to deal with losing my first child after thinking i couldn't have kids my whole life. i ended up pregnant with my beautiful rainbow baby graham 2 months later and so i kept eating to comfort my previous loss as well as the new stress and anxiety of possibly losing this baby too. once he was here we spent a lot of time in and out of the hospital and he is great and healthy now but all of this took a toll on me and my mental health. i got #ptsd and #postpartum #anxietyanddepression as well as gaining back 110 of the original 135 i had lost. i am in a rut...this is me putting my pride on the line to ask for help. so if you want to offer support, recipes, a shoulder, a funny video, a workout buddy, or need any of those things yourself please reach out to me. let's #snatchthewigoff2018 and #getitstarted #healthyweightloss #selfharm #sexualassault #silencethesabateur

text:
i used to have the belief that i had to “do it on my own “. that somehow if i had help or relied on others, it invalidated what i did.  it was exhausting, stressful, and lonely. i’ve learned that having help is not a sign of weakness, but is actually a strength.  i now have my tribes that i know i can bounce ideas off of, be vulnerable with, and get support from. 
have you fallen into my old way of thinking? 💖 📸: joanna kosinska

text_retweet:
repost from @belinda_vegan ・・・
all use of animals for food, clothing, entertainment, pets or experimentation involves utilising animals against their will, and - in the vast majority of cases - involves their suffering and deaths. we are brought up to believe in our current society that we need to consume or make use of other animals but this is neither ethical nor necessary. instead, vegans choose to live a lifestyle that respects other animals as sentient individuals whose lives have meaning and do not consume, wear or use animal products or take part in activities which exploit animals. today, being vegan is easy, proven to be healthy and needn't cost more. 
_
being vegan is about living a lifestyle that does not cause suffering, harm or death to animals, and allowing animals to be free to choose the way they want to live. other animals are sentient beings like us, with their own needs, desires and interests. we now know that like us, they can experience a wide range of sensations and emotions such as happiness, pain, pleasure, fear, hunger, sadness, boredom, frustration or contentment. they are aware of the world and what happens to them matters to them. their lives have intrinsic value - they are not inferior beings nor just here as resources or tools for human use. discriminating against non-human animals or believing them to be inferior solely because they belong to a different species is known as speciesism and is as unscientific and unjust as racism or sexism. 
_
embrace veganism🌱

all use of animals for food, clothing, entertainment, pets or experimentation involves utilising animals against their will, and - in the vast majority of cases - involves their suffering and deaths. we are brought up to believe in our current society that we need to consume or make use of other animals but this is neither ethical nor necessary. instead, vegans choose to live a lifestyle that respects other animals as sentient individuals whose lives have meaning and do not consume, wear or use animal products or take part in activities which exploit animals. today, being vegan is easy, proven to be healthy and needn't cost more. 
_
being vegan is about living a lifestyle that does not cause suffering, harm or death to animals, and allowing animals to be free to choose the way they want to live. other animals are sentient beings like us, with their own needs, desires and interests. we now know that like us, they can experience a wide range of sensations and emotions such as happiness, pain, pleasure, fear, hunger, sadness, boredom, frustration or contentment. they are aware of the world and what happens to them matters to them. their lives have intrinsic value - they are not inferior beings nor just here as resources or tools for human use. discriminating against non-human animals or believing them to be inferior solely because they belong to a different species is known as speciesism and is as unscientific and unjust as racism or sexism. 
_
embrace veganism🌱

text:
and so i apologized. i made a mistake, and i caused real harm. i followed directions. i #honor the request to change. and i forgive myself because my #intention was #pure and #good even if #limited to my own line of sight. i’ll continue doing calculations and explorations of this method with other people, knowing that the work must circulate even if i hurt some good people. 
#reparations is a #messy process. first, there is no one method or formula for determining reparations.

so much of the violence we experience is personal and personalized. how it affects us is embodied and related to who we are in this earth walk. that's why this method was designed for people like you and #metoo.

second, calculating reparations is always an economic and #spiritual practice. above all, the spiritual dimension of this method is central, and #survivors must lead each initiative. the point is to foster #healing, not pay for therapy and legal costs, and give people the support we require to create solutions for ourselves and our beloved communities. so, what does healing mean for you as a survivor of the violence you seek to stop? given your daily life and needs at this time, what do you need to put in place to learn and apply the method?

from a purely economic perspective, what aspects of healing can financial reparations facilitate? this question is the most direct, but it isn't as simple as it sounds. for example, you might #desire therapy and know that therapists cost a rate of, say $60-250 an hour in your town. what if no therapist in your local #beloved community speaks your mother language of #arabic or #quechua or #japanese and that's the language in which you sense the world? what is the honest price tag for your therapy sessions if you have to travel three hours to see a therapist who shares your cultural, linguistic, ancestral #perspective? 
the whole #shebang is on youtube as a video or linkedin as an article.

text:
sound on - our musical is based on a true story.  wanda savage was living #metoo back in the 1920s when women’s major commodity, if not the only one, was sex (especially if you were a minority trying to move up and make a life for yourself). very very sad, but true. so many women would try to marry men who were richer or white etc. to raise their own social status and do better for themselves and their children sometimes at high costs like abuse etc.. this video snippet was at our staged reading. we decided at this point in reading to have the actors step away from the stands and act it out a little because this scene is so dramatic. don’t you wish you knew what is going to happen next and who she’s pointing the gun at????

text:
things we need to learn from goddess lakshmi, 
1) we aren't limited. lakshmi incarnated from the abyssal ocean. and we also incarnate everytime we come back home from the labyrinthine war this world is. we shed the battered skin and break ourself free from the bones that no longer support us. we take a new form, everytime the war brings us down. 
2) lakshmi was called arrogant by her own husband for self-praising — for recognizing her worth, for verbalising her importance. today we find her in homes and temples across the street. humans thronging around her statues, wishing for prosperity. 
3) scream your worthiness on the top of your lungs. you are important and people pull you down because they want you to fold your legs and sit down with a plastered smile on your face. rip off the glares you get by slicing them with answers and more questions.
4) maa lakshmi was stated incomplete for not bearing a child.  later she adopted lord ganesha and promised to bestow him with love and affection. you don't have to carry the burden of another soul if your own skin is scarred. your healing can not wait. your recovery is a rare flower that is hidden inside your own heart. find it, water it, grow it. let it bloom so ravishingly that every doubt you have about your esteem gets vanished under it's calm shade. 
5) despite being the goddess of wealth and fortune she was doubted for raising a child because she never stayed at one place. because her nature was agile. and never will you see her without her son even today. people will tell us thousand things to do and not to do and we'll be judged on the basis of their assumptions but what will matter is how we decide to take hold of what requires ours and only ours attention.

let's open the most darkest room inside our minds, and start cleaning the mess locked up there. what awaits for us is  edification, we just need to find the hidden chaos that's blocking the light.

i have something personal to share... this year has felt like a particularly hard year to be a woman to me. so many people i knew were sharing their stories online of sexual assault and abuse, and i found myself shying away from social media. it hurt to read yet another story of harassment or abuse.  what's sad is that i wasn't shocked by it, i was just worn down. and yet through this breaking open, a quiet solidarity formed; a holding of space for people to share their stories. a community was being born. this roaring back of survivors saying, "that happened to me too, and i believe you." it was a place for healing. —
sexual abuse and assault are happening to women, men, and gender non-conforming people all over the world. it does not discriminate by ethnicity, class, or political affiliation. this is a human issue. a little over a month ago i watched dr. christine blasey-ford's testimony along with the rest of the country. i don't know her. i don't know her alleged attacker. i wasn't there. but her story sounded very familiar to me. i recognized the quiver in her voice. i was sick to my stomach. and i couldn't sleep. i finally got up in the middle of the night, sat at the piano and put my feelings on paper. afterwards i felt better and went to bed at peace. the next day i went in studio with my dear friend @jameyjaz and recorded what i had written, which turned out to be this song. the following day i found the visionary and director of this project, @vanessabeletic. and now a month later, here we are debuting the music video, which was unlike any experience i've ever had. —
to the brave survivors and allies who gave of their time to bare their souls in this video, thank you. you owned your power and i am so humbled that i was there to witness it. it was a day of transformation. —
i stand with anyone who has experienced sexual or domestic assault of any kind. i believe you. i am your tribe. there are others too[...]

text:
join us tomorrow (11.14) from 7-9pm for radical self care now! @terrycrews will share how he harnesses the courage to be so honest about his past. 
in june 2018, actor terry crews appeared in front of the senate judiciary committee alongside rise founder amanda nguyen to share his story as a victim of sexual assault and to advocate for the sexual assault survivors’ bill of rights. crews has also spoken publicly this year about growing up with an abusive father and has been vocal about his experiences and in support for the #metoo movement. 
many fans have praised his bravery for speaking out and thanked him for giving a voice to male survivors of sexual assault. 
american sign language (asl) interpretation will be provided.

please rsvp by following the eventbrite link on our facebook.

text_retweet:
#repost @whywomendontleave
・・・
sometimes you go through things in your life that are awful. hell on earth.  some things are not okay. sometimes you get dealt a really bad hand. forcing yourself to be "positive" and see the bright side of a horrible event isn't necessarily the right way to handle things.  when i was diagnosed with breast cancer,  everyone in my life kept shoving rays of sunshine down my throat. "stay strong" and "fight like a girl"  everyone deals with trauma differently. i was just trying to get through each moment. the year of 2016 was pure hell for me. i was actually kicked out of a breast cancer support group because i was not "positive enough " of course i was going through chemotherapy and having an allergic reaction to the treatment but no one would listen to me. i was just accused of not being "positive enough”.
-
there's some similarities between dealing with domestic abuse and cancer. these are two topics that make people very uncomfortable.  so well meaning people, and others want you to be strong and just move on. but sometimes that's because it's what they need, not what you need. it's okay to say "wow what happened to you was horrible" that's validation and we all should have the freedom to feel whatever emotions we need to.  that's not the same as behaving however you want. feelings and actions are two very different things. feelings aren't good or bad,  it's what you do with them. start where you are. i have been dealt some really lousy cards, but that doesn't mean i have to give up. i feel, i process and i keep moving forward.  that's how you survive. you don't quit.

text:
we need to stop teaching girls that sex is risky behavior, leads to unwanted pregnancy and stds, and teach her the value of trust, safety, and mutual respect. we will teach her that sex can be healing, a source of joy and true connection. we will teach her that her body is hers, and hers alone and that her self-worth is only dependent on her values and beliefs. she will grow up learning that she invites a man in when she is ready, we will give her language to express her desires and needs, and she will move through the world owning her sexuality.
•
•
•
because most of us realized that was missing for us. what came up the most in sundays circle in resounding unanimity was how sex had been a source of embarrassment, shame, pain and coercion. many of us had sexual experiences in the gray area between borderline rape or a date gone wrong. we still aren’t sure, but nevertheless it left us numb, paralyzed and deeply hurt. sexual assault had been all to commonly shared between us, and many of us had experienced detachment from our bodies in one way or another as a form of protection.  at the circle, we talked about how the definition around mutual consent needs to expand, and how to create a dialogue between partners on how to wholeheartedly say yes to sex every step of the way, and how that would create more fulfilling sexual experiences.
•
•
•

text:
"panty portrait: cunt" from the panty project, 5 of 51
.

fiber art, archival pigment print on museum cotton rag, 
19 x 14 inches
.
the panty project is an ongoing social practice project. participants, womxn and those who identify as womxn, courageously share with me their stories of experienced gendered transgressions and violent aggressions, whether cultural and/or interpersonal. participants write a word or phrase onto the panel of their selected undergarment; i hand-embroider over their mark-making and photograph them as if they have been taken off. this work addresses the inherent misogyny within our language, and the consequential "essestializing" of womxn, which reduces womxn, and those who identify as womxn, to "less than." this work is about healing and transcendence. 
womxn's long-silenced voices must be heard.
.

the panty project is an ongoing social practice project. paicipants, womxn and those who identify as womxn, courageously share with me their stories of experienced gendered transgressions and violent aggressions, whether cultural and/or interpersonal. paicipants write a word or phrase onto the panel of their selected undergarment; i hand-embroider over their mark-making and photograph them as if they have been taken off. this work addresses the inherent misogyny within our language, and the consequential "essestializing" of womxn, which reduces womxn, and those who identify as womxn, to "less than." this work is about healing and transcendence. 
womxn's long-silenced voices must be heard.

text:
lorde goes after kanye west and kid cudi for suggesting they "stole" her set design

email instagram
update: set designer es devlin has seemingly responded to lorde 's accusations, posting a photo to instagram of a floating box she designed for the english national opera in 2007. noting the date, it appears she first used the design concept over 10 years ago. "carmen by georges bizet , english national opera 2007," the designer, who has worked with kanye west since 2005 and has also worked with lorde, captioned the post.
tmz reports that devlin designed kanye's floating stage for his saint pablo tour in 2016, and worked with lorde on a similar box look the following year for coachella, a similar design was later used for lorde's tour.
lorde is taking some issue with kanye west and kid cudi 's most recent concert at tyler, the creator 's camp flog gnaw festival in los angeles. the duo performed under the name kids see ghosts, which is also the name of the album they released together in june.
on thursday, the "royals" singer posted a few photos on instagram comparing her 2017 tour set—including her headlining stint at coachella—alongside pictures from camp flog gnaw. in both instances, a transparent and enclosed stage-like area is suspended above the ground. kanye and kid cudi were both in the box, whereas lorde stood in front of it in her photos. other dancers and performers were in the hanging stage during her concert.
lorde, however, did not call out kids see ghosts by name on her instagram story, but a picture can be worth a thousand words. in one part of her story, she wrote, "i'm proud of the work i do and it's flattering when other artists feel inspired by it, to the extent that they try it on themselves."
she added, "but don't steal—not from women or from anyone else—in 2018 or ever." read
lorde weighs in on the #metoo movement and amplifying women of color's voices getty images
lorde has never shied away from speaking her mind, and wears her heart on her sleeve—literally. at the 2018 grammys , she had a piece of paper attached to the back https://www.eonline.com/news/986736/lorde-goes-after-kanye-west-and-kid-cudi-for-suggesting-they-stole-her-set-design

text:
#metoo 
trigger warning rape/sexual assault
i’ve been terrified to post this on social media but it needs to be talked about and i’m sick of hiding. when i was four i was raped by a nonfamily member. i didn’t even mutter a word something terrible and traumatic happened to me when i was so young until i was 18 years old. i was just starting therapy and after nearly a month of just talking about my depression and anxiety i felt like i was gonna explode from holding this secret i had in. it’s been almost two years since i told anyone what happened to me. my fear was that people may look at my differently or see me as a victim, which is the opposite that i’d ever wanna be seen as. i’m living with ptsd and an anxiety disorder but i’m making progress everyday mentally. i’ve been growing and processing this trauma working so hard and putting all my energy into therapy and healing recently. i just feel like i had to put this out publicly finally and stop feeling like i need to hide my past and feel ashamed for it. i’m healing more and more everyday and finally learning to love and accept myself. it’s been almost 16 years since the trauma happened and everyday i relive it and see my abusers face. but i know with my hard work in therapy and the love and endless support i have from friends and family will heal my mental wounds eventually. if anyone gets anything from this post i just want you to know whatever gender you identify with, whatever sexuality, religion etc. you are safe to open up about your trauma and ask for professional help. i’m forever thankful i finally bit the bullet and got a therapist and talked about my past. it’s been extremely life changing and the person i’ve become over the past few years didn’t feel attainable until now. you are never alone and your story can now safely be told. never be afraid to reach out for help my friends.
name: fiona mackenzie

text:
i’ve had something on my #heart recently and i’ve been trying to find the right time to talk (*ahem* post about it) and i realized today that there is never really a good #time ❤️ anxiety. yes, that word. did you know that about 40 million americans suffer from anxiety? 😳 i hate that it exists and i hate that there are so many people out there that feel hopeless and alone. well i’m here to tell you that you are not 👏🏻 alone 👏🏻 i struggle almost daily and i made the decision long ago that i didn’t want meds to deal with my issues i wanted god to help me. i know there’s someone out there that needs this and i pray the right eyes 👀 will read this post ❤️ i know how you feel.. you worry constantly, your brain never shuts off, & it’s almost impossible to relax. your heart races (sometimes for no reason) and you can be triggered by literally anything. you hate even talking about it because people look at you like your crazy or they roll their eyes like, “here she goes again.” sound familiar? 🙋🏻‍♀️ people that don’t suffer from anxiety can not relate to you and that’s just how it is. 
i wanted to share a few things that have helped me over the years and i know they can help you, too ❤️ (1) jesus. literally the only way i am (halfway 😂) sane today. i pray and read my bible every day and i know without a doubt i would be medicated if it wasn’t for that. (2) go outside. fresh air and open space do wonders for our bodies. even if you go outside and do nothing. just go outside. ❤️ (3) listen to uplifting music. if you’re local to me, 106.9 and 94.1 are my favorite stations. (4) learn that it’s okay to say, “no.” this is a hard one for me but it has helped me more times than i can tell you. your anxiety will be worse if you are constantly saying “yes” to everything someone asks you to do. you are one person and if your plate is full, that’s on you. i could list about 45 more but i feel these 4 things have been the most helpful with my anxiety ❤️❤️❤️ i truly hope this helps someone out there, i know it was put on my heart for a reason and please do not hesitate to reach out if you need someone to talk to or pray with! 👏🏻 i love you guys, thanks for reading ❤️

(4) learn that it’s okay to say, “no.” this is a hard one for me but it has helped me more times than i can tell you. your anxiety will be worse if you are constantly saying “yes” to everything someone asks you to do. you are one person and if your plate is full, that’s on you. i could list about 45 more but i feel these 4 things have been the most helpful with my anxiety ❤️❤️❤️ i truly hope this helps someone out there, i know it was put on my heart for a reason and please do not hesitate to reach out if you need someone to talk to or pray with! 👏🏻 i love you guys, thanks for reading ❤️

text:
muitas empresas não podem demiti-lo, mas os trabalhadores ainda têm muitos motivos para evitar um romance de escritório. na segunda-feira, uma empresa informou que todos os funcionários de empresa devem divulgar os romances de escritório. seu novo código de conduta diz “necessário informar seu gerente ou outro ponto de contato apropriado sobre mudanças em relacionamentos pessoais que possam ser relevantes para o seu papel”.
esses relacionamentos nem sempre terminam bem. um em cada três relacionamentos românticos terminará em pelo menos uma pessoa sendo demitida, de acordo com uma pesquisa com 150 executivos de recursos humanos realizada por uma empresa de recrutamento. a pesquisa constatou que 17% dos empregadores escolheram se mudar para uma filial da empresa, alguns foram para um departamento diferente, e 5% desses casos levaram a litígios.
no entanto, um em cada quatro trabalhadores afirma ter envolvido (ou atualmente) um relacionamento com um colega. mas na era #metoo, as relações de escritório podem representar um grande risco para as empresas, pois dois terços dos executivos de rh entrevistados disseram que seus departamentos tiveram que lidar com as consequências de um romance fracassado ou inadequado no local de trabalho.
cerca de 60% dos empregadores tinham algum tipo de política formal em relação a relacionamentos românticos no escritório, enquanto outros 10% das empresas disseram que informaram aos funcionários que os assuntos foram desaprovados. entre as empresas que tinham uma política escrita, 70% proibiram relacionamentos entre gerentes e subordinados, enquanto quase metade (47%) desencorajou-as. outro terço das empresas disse que lidam com relações de escritório caso a caso.
ainda assim, apesar das preocupações levantadas pelo movimento #metoo, quase dois terços dos entrevistados disseram estar confortáveis com a atual política de assédio sexual e não a reavaliaram. e entre aqueles que revisaram sua política, apenas 25% decidiram atualizá-la.
políticas como essas não são as únicas mudanças no rastro do movimento #metoo. no inverno passado, muitas empresas optaram por reduzir suas festas de fim de ano após as alegações de má conduta sexual.

.
. —green tara, the compassionate female bodhisattva, prayed to by women for a thousand years. .
.
.

text:
i know, there are many things, in my childhood, that i've either forgotten or just have partial memories of. why, who knows? however, there are somethings, that stick with you forever, even if you don't remember verbatim, what was said and exact timelines. trauma can go in either direction; causing you to shut down, to protect yourself or causing you, to remember and relive, the incident(s) forever. if you're lucky, you'll remember but not get stuck. 
regardless, if and when you remember #speakup and #speakout. i would caution, that you preface, your disclosure, revealing the partial memories but if you know, you were a victim of a #pedophile #childabuser #childmolester #childrapist and #sexualdeviant, do not remain silent. tell what you remember to someone so it can be a record, for if and when others, feel safe, to disclose their stories. 
for the benefit of yourself and others, past, present and maybe future victims, n-e-v-e-r choose silence. silence only benefits the #abusers. there's no shame in speaking up.

#nevillearchibald #carnovan musicteacher

text:
i was misdiagnosed and consequently wrongfully medicated for years until i had a proper evaluation done by a specialist. the company i worked for at the time paid $5000 for me be assessed and diagnosed by a top practitioner. it was only then that i was told that i had been misdiagnosed and that i have complex post traumatic stress disorder. 🌼
so many of my symptoms were overlapping with other illnesses that it took someone who truly knew what they were doing to get to the bottom of it. this is often the case and the reasons why so many people are misdiagnosed and never get the treatment they need. a proper diagnosis landed me a referral to women's college hospital for what i honestly believe is the best trauma treatment program in toronto.
🌼
why am i sharing this? because as i continue to heal and learn to thrive with c-ptsd, i am committed to providing as much support as i can to other women who are still at the beginning of their healing journeys. it breaks my heart to see so many of them misdiagnosed and wrongfully treated and to see them remaining unwell. 🌼
self-advocacy is so important. and that can only happen when we educate and empower ourselves with knowledge and understanding. doing so makes us one of the best resources we have. it's why i continue to share so much about mental health, especially trauma.
🌼
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

.
.
.
.

i was misdiagnosed and consequently wrongfully medicated for years until i had a proper evaluation done by a specialist. the company i worked for at the time paid $5000 for me be assessed and diagnosed by a top practitioner. it was only then that i was told that i had been misdiagnosed and that i have complex post traumatic stress disorder. 🌼
so many of my symptoms were overlapping with other illnesses that it took someone who truly knew what they were doing to get to the bottom of it. this is often the case and the reasons why so many people are misdiagnosed and never get the treatment they need. a proper diagnosis landed me a referral to women's college hospital for what i honestly believe is the best trauma treatment program in toronto.
🌼
why am i sharing this? because as i continue to heal and learn to thrive with c-ptsd, i am committed to providing as much suppo as i can to other women who are still at the beginning of their healing journeys. it breaks my hea to see so many of them misdiagnosed and wrongfully treated and to see them remaining unwell. 🌼
self-advocacy is so impoant. and that can only happen when we educate and empower ourselves with knowledge and understanding. doing so makes us one of the best resources we have. it is why i continue to share so much about mental health, especially trauma.
🌼

text:
she likes to paint pictures of herself
and giant-like men in a dwarf-like world
she knows of tales which she never tells
most of them she experienced herself

like that one of the bad wolf,
who comes from time to time
and everytime after he demands from her
not to say a single word,
or he will punish her horribly

when her mommy takes her into her arms
she would like best to cry and confess everything
but she is scared and she is ashamed of herself
she doesn't know what to do and tries to look away

when the bad wolf comes every now and then
who comes from time to time
and everytime after he demands from her
not to say a single word,
or he will punish her horribly

she is shy like a young timid fawn
nobody hardly notices her, for she doesn't talk much
she likes best to stay to herself alone
praying to god and wishing

that the bad wolf never returns again
and with a stronghold on her neck demands,
not to say a single word to anybody,
or he will punish her horribly

sie malt gern bilder von sich selbst
und riesengroßen männern in einer zwergenwelt
sie weiß geschichten, die sie nie erzählt
die meisten davon hat sie selber erlebt
wie die vom bösen wolf
der hin und wieder kommt
und jedes mal danach von ihr verlangt,
dass sie niemals ein sterbenswörtchen sagt
weil er sie dafür sonst fürchterlich bestraft

wenn ihre mami sie in den arm nimmt
würde sie am liebsten weinen und alles gestehen,
doch sie hat angst und sie schämt sich
sie weiß keinen rat und versucht wegzusehen
wenn der böse wolf hin und wieder kommt
und jedes mal danach von ihr verlangt,
dass sie niemals ein sterbenswörtchen sagt,
weil er sie dafür sonst fürchterlich bestraft

sie ist so scheu wie ein reh
man nimmt sie kaum wahr, denn sie redet nicht viel
sie bleibt am liebsten für sich allein
betet zu gott und wünscht sich dabei,
dass der böse wolf niemals wieder kommt
und mit festem griff um ihren hals verlangt
dass sie keinem ein sterbenswörtchen sagt
weil er sie dafür sonst fürchterlich bestraft
dass sie keinem ein sterbenswörtchen sagt
weil er sie dafür sonst fürchterlich bestraft

text:
the #faxx are in: did you know that ‘gender lens investing’ is a thing…and that’s it’s on the rise? index and mutual funds that specifically invest in companies that promote gender parity are popping up on global exchanges as more and more research proves female leadership is profitable and lessens risk. they have requirements for the companies they invest in like: a minimum number of women in board positions or, a specific % of women in key management roles, or companies with the highest percentage of female managers in their respective sectors. there’s the parity portfolio, state street's fund, with the ticker symbol she, the glenmede women in leadership fund ("gwilx”), barclays women in leadership total return index, and probably the best known: the pax ellevate global women’s leadership fund (pxwex), which has outperformed the msci world index for the one-year and three-year periods ending september 30, 2018. proof that #womenmeanbusiness…and investors are listening!
.
.
.
.
.

text:
a veces no somos conscientes,
pero pasa, y mucho... ⬇️⬇️⬇️ 21:00 horas... hola😊
......
voy a salir, no me esperes, no sé a que hora llegaré.
......
sí, saldré maquillada, con la raya del ojo hecha, con los labios pintados de rojo.
......
no, no creo que lleve abrigo, hace bastante calor, estamos en pleno mes de agosto.
......
por favor, que vivimos en canarias.
......
voy a salir con las compañeras del trabajo.
......
no, no va ningún chico con nosotras. ......
no sé, todavía no lo tenemos claro.
......
me cambio en casa de macarena.
......
no, todavía no sé que me voy a poner, las botas de cuero seguro.
......
no, no sé si podré estar pendiente al teléfono, vamos a ir a una discoteca, hay mucho ruido.
......
sí, intentaré mandarte algún wasap. ......
sí, también alguna foto.
......
no, no beberé mucho. ......
no sé lo que me voy a poner no seas pesado.
......
a mí me encanta ese vestido, tengo las piernas muy bonitas. ......
bueno, si tú lo ves así...
......
bueno, me voy que ya han venido a recogerme.
......
no, no me olvido de ti.
......
sí, me portaré bien te lo prometo. ......
no, solo estaré con las chicas. ......
yo también te quiero. 
adiós.

text:
it becomes increasingly more important to listen to one another and to realize this is the culture we live in. the dismissal of events that don’t result in sexual assault are not minuscule, they are still terrifying, traumatizing and real. for in those moments, she was wondering (i was wondering) is this going to happen to me again? and afterwards when she realizes she’s safe, she’ll rethink the situation over and over, ask herself if she overreacted, and feel humiliated to talk about it, because it didn’t happen this time. 
if someone you know tries to open up to you about something that did or didn’t happen, please stop and listen, i promise you have no comprehension of how hard it was for her to have decided she felt safe enough to do so with you. just listen to her.

text:
i am so so jazzed to have @mburton0214 teach this workshop at @lolaretreat. i don't know one woman who has not been affected by the diet, wellness and beauty industries.
---- how the diet and wellness industry is making you broke on every level

the health and wellness industry has been pioneered and dominated by women. women are also primarily responsible for making the health and wellness industry a multi trillion dollar industry. our current culture dictates that not only should women be and do it all, they should look (and feel!) flawlessly amazing while accomplishing their goals and living their best lives (insert eye roll here). even in the empowered #metoo era, women are still being convinced that they need to invest their money and energy in the dreams promised by the diet and wellness industry in order to even deserve a healthy, happy and successful life (yes, i’m looking at you, goop). in this session you’ll learn how and why the diet and wellness industry is seducing you - as a smart and motivated woman - to place your hard earned dollars and precious headspace into their hands. in this session melissa burton, a former marketing manager and current registered dietitian nutritionist (and registered yoga teacher), will help you understand the depth, breath and power of diet culture and how to lessen its impact on your wallet, mind, heart and soul.

text:
the shadows that fall across our face…
_
the darkness that appears in our eyes…
_
the light we once had, almost out….
_
it can be a lonely place when you have a secret. when you are protecting something or someone that doesn’t deserve it.
_
surrounded by people who love and care about you but not being able to mutter a word.
_
so you keep quiet, and you pretend you are ok.
_
you find the strength to show up as the person you wished you was.
_
for me, it was one of confidence and strength… but inside i was crumbling.
_
inside, i was scared.
_
being held prisoner because you just wanted to forget and pretend so you hold on… hold on to that belief that maybe …maybe… you will wake up and you would have got through it without any heartache.
_
without destruction…
_
without anyone knowing the darkness we are trying to hide.
_
the darkness we are trying to avoid.
_
the thing is… we cant ignore the darkness, we cant ignore the shadows.
_
they are there, just like the light.
_
instead of trying to avoid them, we need to look passed them…
_
we need to dance through them, so we can see the light.
_
because for what makes us whole is the good and the bad, the dark and the light.
_
i would never have known my strength if i had not been weak.
_
i would never know love if i didn’t know heartache.
_
i would never have known how brightly i can shine if i didn’t know how dark it could get.
_
its time to stop hiding in the shadows of the person you are meant to be.
_
its time to take back your light.
_
its time to be all of you….
_
when you are ready… the link is in the bio x

text: you know how i know? because when people can't see you when you're communicating they will treat you differently than people treat you in person because their imagination is more engaged. and it's even worse over text in that they will interpret inaccurately due to them having to assume intentions or your emotions. particularly if you're at an awareness they're not, forget trying for the message to be understood. that's no reason to fault the person. but it's also no reason to take it personally whatsoever.  it's even the same as with your physical form. for women, wear a sexy outfit to show your friends and now men you don't like will look at you like you are available to them and it will feel gross. for men, dressing down or having super short hair will create fear responses in public. i remember a long time ago i went to the track at like 5am and because of sports i had shaved my head. this woman in her 30s was stretching her leg on the railing, sees me and says barely under her breath "shit...". i look at her for a second with an expression of wtf 😡and start walking. when i got back around she was gone. then this one time i was dressed up in a blazer with longer hair at a club and some girl grabbed my butt. #metoo . so the point is, people are going to do stupid shit and believe stupid shit. recognize the variety in responses. don't take it personally. a lot of people are fucking stupid, and they don't deserve the consideration for you to change your reality and feel shit emotions with them when there are so many good people out there also. next! #entrepreneur #coldcalling

text:
nancy pelosi’s “#election night speech” sounded a lot like #trump with calls of “a new day in america”, “ending special interests”, “lower the costs of prescription drugs”, “rebuilding infrastructure”, and “draining the #swamp”. these emotional calls coupled with her nationalist call for “unity” in “one country”, show us that yet again, the “resistance” of the other fraction of the capitalist #class is a competitive sport. the #democrats are not only willing, but seeking unity with the #fascist consolidation happening under trump. in 1932, in an attempt to address growing divisions among the german #bourgeoisie and counter the growing disdain of the masses with the crisis of german capitalism, president paul von hindenburg appointed adolf hitler as chancellor when the nazis were still a minority party. in 1933, fascists burned down the german #parliament. the 1933 “enabling act” shut down basic bourgeois-democratic #rights and the fascist consolidation was officially solidified. normal bourgeois #democracy in germany would not return till after the bloody 2nd inter-imperialist war. millions were exterminated by fascism’s brutal capitalist efficiency. the demagoguery and opportunism of these politicians knows no limits. 
the class lines have been drawn folks. we are at war. electoral #politics is the #political field of our class enemy. we must change the battleground, #organize and face the enemy on our turf – in the work places, in the streets. we aren’t divided by gender, color, or ethnicity, we are divided by antagonistic class interests in a world order which functions off our sweat and blood! the #resistance" is a paper tiger. workers realities are getting worse not because one or the other captain runs the ship, but the ship itself is sinking. these bourgeois politicians exist to represent the interests of different fractions of capital in the capitalist state. the only way forward for us is the #unity of the #workingclass. we must organize! we must uprise! there is no possible alternative for the masses of humanity outside our #organization. if you agree, hit us up!

#mondaymotivation #classtruggle #metoo #ideological #fieldofstruggle #whichsideareyouon

text:
#feedback 📝📱 ✍🏻🗣
jeg har haft æren af at have en unik ung mand på briksen.

jeg bliver så glad hver gang, en klient fortæller den forskel behandlingen har gjort 💆🏻‍♂️💫 #bodysds 
det var bestemt en ære, at få lov at høre hans fortælling om livet. 
hvordan nogle gange, så vælter hele 🌬 korthuset 😔. man prøver at få hverdagen til at fortsætte, men .. det virker ikke 
jeg har kæmpe respekt for han var klar på, at genfinde balancen i kroppen 💆🏻‍♂️ jeg elsker den her del af livet ❤️ tænk sig at kunne bidrage til det. 
vi mister alle balancen indimellem. når det sker, så husk at hjælpe kroppen med at give slip #givslip 
hjernen 🧠 husker nogen gange - kroppen husker alt. 
mange har kroniske smerter, stress, fordøjelsesproblemer, angst uden at vide hvorfor. 
tit kan der være et bagvedliggende traume/en sorg , der ligger uforløst i kroppen. 
vores muskulatur kan være sammentrukket, og spændte uden evnen til at give slip. 
i feks. nakke, lænd, ryg og skuldre. 
jeg er glad for jeg valgte behandler vejen ❤️ det giver mening #inmanyways 
alt kan ske 😉
#bodysds #bodytherapy #kropsterapi #kroppenhusker #altkanske #elevbehandling 
#myworld #balancedbody #happymind #gladkrop #itmakesence #restoreyourself #feedback #treatment #myclientsrock ❤️

text:
day 3 #nakedwerise photo challenge 
c o u r a g e
i always like to think of courage as heart courage from our core truth.
although we might never be ready to forgive those who have violated us, still feel like we need to protect ourselves and yet how do we find the courage to take the first step to rectify the out-of-balance masculine within ourselves?  where are we mimicking the patriarchy and acting as our own violator? where can we soften our heart in the areas that we act hard and firm when it is not our true nature?

how can you support your inner masculine and forgive yourself? how about humming to that wound itself, humming to feel seen, safe and supported. see how that vibrates within you. 🌹

what other steps of courage can you take to assist the divine masculine rising and praise the men in your life?? 🌈thank you to #wowzalodge for the inspiration of humming for self-healing ❤

text:
sometimes the narcissist will tell you that another person (such as a coworker or one of your friends) is flirting with him/her. this is done to:
. ▫1 - stir up feelings of insecurity inside you ▫2 - help them feel like they're desirable to other people ▫3 - make you start doing more to please the narc because you fear that you might lose him/her ▫4 - create a rivalry between you & the other person. (and if the person is your friend, it may be an attempt to destroy the friendship/isolate you from your friend).
.
.
this, ladies & gentlemen, is called "triangulation". it's only one of several types, but the goal is always the same: turn two people against each other while the narc appears to be the hero or the "good guy" within the triangle.
.

text:
calling all women! women have been fighting to have equal rights for generations. the right to be equal to men, the right to vote, the right to have the same pay in the work place, the right to control our bodies.. the list goes on. we’ve fought so hard through the years and while we’ve accomplished many tribulations, we have a long way to go. we hear so many women with health care stories, work place stories, #metoo stories...we hear so many of our sisters bare their heart with these gut wrenching words, and it changed so many things in our world. it started movements all over the map. and it has taught us that our strength comes from holding one another hands, seeing each other and coming together to fight our fight. women from all different backgrounds, all different races, all different faces- from my heart, i see you. my dear friend @aijiaofficial has released her music video for her beautiful song “for you”. i’m begging you, women (and men) to watch it, to feel it, and to see these women and all women around you and know we are all fighting this battle. you are not alone. i’m so happy and so proud to call this woman my friend, because she’s about to touch many hearts with this one. ❤️ *link down below! •
•
https://www.bustle.com/p/how-the-christine-blasey-ford-testimony-inspired-singer-aijia-to-make-a-powerful-music-video-about-metoo-watch-13131021

text:
it’s not about what i see, it’s about what you see!
.
we recently watched cool runnings with our kids. there are so many good take aways in that movie! i especially loved the scene where yul brenner takes junior over to the mirror and asks him what he sees. a shy junior responds that he only sees himself in the mirror to which yul tells him what he sees. he sees pride! he sees power! junior asks him if he really sees those things and yul confidently says yes. but the next line is what i thought was so wonderful. yul then tells junior “it’s not about what i see, it’s about what you see.” yul continues to tell junior what he sees and makes junior repeat what he is saying. it’s an energetic scene in which you watch as junior begins to believe the things that yul is having him say to himself.
.
so let’s talk positive affirmations for a minute. what are they? are they lies we tell ourselves to make us feel better? no! positive affirmations are a way to re-train your brain to notice the wonderful and amazing things about you!!!! because they are there! but so often they’re overlooked and over shadowed by comparisons and self doubt and we need to stop doing that to ourselves. we need to realize and become empowered by the amazing gifts god has given us.
.
so what do you see when you look at yourself? go ahead, make some positive comments about you! yes, at first it’s going to feel very one-with-the-earth-ish but keep going! this practice does get easier and eventually you’ll begin to see it in yourself rather than just telling it to yourself. you know that energetic transformation that junior had in cool runings? you can have it too!
.
here are my two favorite positive affirmations right now: i am strong. i can do hard things.
.
you’re turn, what are some of your favorite positive affirmations?
.
want more info on positive affirmations? i just listened to @bicepsafterbabies podcast #4 titled 5 things i want you to know as you start your fitness journey and it is a-mazing!!!

مجله زندگی ایده آل - نسرین خسروشاهی: «تجاوز» واژه‌ای است كه بار منفی زیادی دارد. وقتی صحبت از «تجاوز جنسی» به میان می‌آید این كلمه بار منفی بیشتری پیدا می‌كند. اگر پای درددل فردی كه قربانی تجاوز یا آزارجنسی شده بنشینید، او این اتفاق را دردناك‌ترین تجربه زندگی خود می‌داند طوری كه انگار قرار نیست هیچ‌وقت آن را فراموش كند و همیشه با آن درگیر است. بخشی از این احساس دردناك مربوط به حسی است كه این فرد از جامعه می‌گیرد و بخشی از آن خشونتی است كه به زنانگی فرد اعمال شده است.

تجاوز به عنف معمولا دو نوع عارضه در پی دارد، عارضه زودهنگام و عارضه دیرهنگام. از مهم‌ترین عوارض زودهنگام می‌توان به حالت شوكی كه در فرد ایجاد می‌شود، اشاره كرد. او حالت ناراحتی شدید و بهت‌زدگی دارد. احساس طرد شدن از اجتماع و این فكر كه به دلیل گناه نكرده مورد تحقیر و تنبیه قرار گرفته است

یكی از مهم‌ترین عوارضی كه بلافاصله بعد از حادثه بروز می‌كند، حالت اختلال استرس بعد از حادثه یا ptsd است، به نحوی كه فرد صحنه‌های تجاوز را دوباره فلش‌بك می‌زند، آنها را دوباره تجربه می‌كند و حتی گاهی حالت دفاعی شدید پیدا می‌كند. در این وضعیت او كناره‌گیری می‌كند و دلش می‌خواهد كسی او را نبیند و با او صحبت نكند، ضمن آنكه فعالیت‌های سیستم عصبی‌‌اش زیاد می‌شود، یعنی پاسخش به محرك‌های محیطی مانند صدا و نور افزایش می‌یابد. 
او نمی‌تواند به كسی اعتماد کرده یا با شخصی ارتباط برقرار كند. در این حالت ممكن است به خودكشی و مرگ فكر كند و آرزوی مردن داشته باشد.  اگر زمینه مشكلات روانی در او دیده شود این احتمال وجود دارد كه دچار افسردگی شیدایی یا همان افسردگی دوقطبی شود. توهم‌های شنوایی و بینایی، هذیان، خنده‌های بی‌معنی، خشم بی‌جهت و... از عوارض دیگر این اتفاق است.
فردی كه مورد تجاوز قرار گرفته در طولانی‌مدت نسبت به رابطه جنسی حس بدی پیدا می‌كند و از آن متنفر می‌شود. دردهای آمیزشی و‌ تنفر از جنس مرد و‌ بدبینی به جنس مخالف از دیگر عوارض تجاوز است. او سعی می‌كند از مردها دوری كرده، حتی شماره تلفن‌اش را عوض كند یا مسیر رفت و آمدش را تغییر دهد. در طولانی‌مدت قابلیت‌های جنسی‌ این فرد از بین می‌رود و اختلال استرس پس از حادثه و افسردگی در او مزمن می‌شود. افسردگی مزمن می‌تواند با توهم و هذیان همراه باشد. 
دردهای جسمانی و شبه‌جسمانی در این فرد زیاد می‌شود. درواقع علائم روانی او تبدیل به علائم جسمانی می‌شود...

افسردگی مزمن می‌تواند با توهم و هذیان همراه باشد . دردهای جسمانی و شبه‌جسمانی در این فرد زیاد می‌شود . درواقع علائم روانی او تبدیل به علائم جسمانی می‌شود ...

بار منفی بیشتری پیدا می‌كند . اگر پای درددل فردی كه قربانی تجاوز یا آزارجنسی شده بنشینید، او این اتفاق را دردناك‌ترین تجربه زندگی خود می‌داند طوری كه انگار قرار نیست هیچ‌وقت آن را فراموش كند و همیشه با آن درگیر است . بخشی از این احساس دردناك مربوط به حسی است كه این فرد از جامعه می‌گیرد و بخشی از آن خشونتی است كه به زنانگی فرد اعمال شده است . تجاوز به عنف معمولا دو نوع عارضه در پی دارد، عارضه زودهنگام و عارضه دیرهنگام . از مهم‌ترین عوارض زودهنگام می‌توان به حالت شوكی كه در فرد ایجاد می‌شود، اشاره كرد . او حالت ناراحتی شدید و بهت‌زدگی دارد . احساس طرد شدن از اجتماع و این فكر كه به دلیل گناه نكرده مورد تحقیر و تنبیه قرار گرفته است یكی از مهم‌ترین عوارضی كه بلافاصله بعد از حادثه بروز می‌كند، حالت اختلال استرس بعد از حادثه یا ptsd است، به نحوی كه فرد صحنه‌های تجاوز را دوباره فلش‌بك می‌زند، آنها را دوباره تجربه می‌كند و حتی گاهی حالت دفاعی شدید پیدا می‌كند . در این وضعیت او كناره‌گیری می‌كند و دلش می‌خواهد كسی او را نبیند و با او صحبت نكند، ضمن آنكه فعالیت‌های سیستم عصبی‌‌اش زیاد می‌شود، زمینه مشكلات روانی در او دیده شود این احتمال وجود دارد كه دچار افسردگی شیدایی یا همان افسردگی دوقطبی شود . توهم‌های شنوایی و بینایی، هذیان، خنده‌های بی‌معنی، خشم بی‌جهت و ... از عوارض دیگر این اتفاق text:
i love this quote and today it absolutely resonates with me. through all my struggles, i found my strength and my voice. and now my purpose is to help others find their strength and voice.
as many of you know, i’ve transitioned from running my beverage company after building it to a national brand and have some exciting news to share!

today is the official launch of my new website! (link in bio above) i’m beyond thrilled to begin this next chapter of my life and share my experiences, stories and challenges with you all to inspire you to be the best version of you! 
other exciting news is that i’m writing a book!  so many times over the years certain things have happened in my business and personal life and people would say to me, “you need to make that a chapter in your book!” i never knew if that day would come, but the day is now here and i can’t wait to share it with you all! 
and i will now be mentoring and consulting and in celebration of the launch of my website i have discounted the introductory one on one consulting and mentoring fees! 
thank you to all the women in my life who have been by my side, supporting me and cheering me on to get me to where i am today! i will be forever grateful and am so honored to now have the platform to inspire others and give back. xo

text: we heard the call and responded!! now we ask you to join us for this critical town hall – “i believe women: sexual assault beyond a reasonable doubt!” featured speaker; @evelyn_mejil, activist, philanthropist, entrepreneur and the author of her new book, “the woman in the mirror - a survivor’s journey into the authentic self,” will be in attendance and also doing a book signing. she’ll be joined by the esteemed group of panelists; dana sussman, deputy commissioner of the @nycchr; cecile noel, commissioner, @nycagainstabuse; dr. tolu olupona, assistant clinical professor of psychiatry at mt sinai medical center; margarita guzman, executive director of the @violence_intervention_program; @reniquaspics, author, freelance writer/producer; scott pennington esq., criminal defense attorney at the pennington law group; moderated by #lisadurdentvpersonality and #apluspanel contributor for wortv’s “ chasing news.” this event is free, thursday, november 15, 2018, 6:30pm – 8:30pm. the acorn theatre, 410 west 42nd st., new york, ny 10036. click link to rsvp: https://bit.ly/2omfthy #metoo! #sexualassault! #believewomen! #ibelievesurvivors! #whyididntreport! #rapeculture! @glaad, @terrycrews, @theresa.oneal, @taranajaneen, @globalfundwomen, @ggenyc, @kaiashivers, @metoomvmt, @nycmayorsoffice, @globalfundwomen.

text:
“adopt the pace of nature: her secret is patience.” - emerson
•
in a world full of “quick fixes” and the world wide web at our fingertips, it’s easy to be impatient. as humans we commonly rush from one place to the next. we are bombarded with all these “quick how to’s” to save time or take shortcuts.
•
but the truth is, in reference to day to day life as well as the process of healing, there really aren’t shortcuts. things worth while, they take time. so don’t kid yourself thinking you’re behind most days because of the fast paced world we live in. don’t feel guilty about not being where you think you “should” be. you can slow down and still work hard. and at the end, when you have reached your goal at your own speed, you will be grateful you took mother nature’s path of patience.
•
we invite you to take a slow, steady pace with us at our retreat in idyllwild, ca march 28-31st, 2019. more info in our bio 💚
•
•
•
•

text:
let’s talk today. 
for everyone, a big part of the #metoo moment is listening to women tell their stories and believing them when they do so.
when a woman says she’s been sexually assaulted, chances of her lying are close to none. here’s why: 
1) sexual assaults are very common. according to stats, every 1 out of 3 woman has undergone sexual assault. 
2) when a woman stands up, she puts a lot at stake. her career, her family, her social life and most importantly, her dignity.

text:
💔👊🛑 please, women...anyone that knows what defeat they thrust upon us... share from my #sisterresistor #wonderwomanwarrior 
@randigloss 
#consequential #consequentialambassadors 
bringing light to disinfect the foul creatures among us!
her story:
three years ago, on this day in 2015, i was raped. these are his words, a text from a conversation we had three days later.

i cannot @ the man who raped me because he blocked me.
he blocked me in fear of the publication of an article that would directly name him.
that article was set to be published in july.
that publication’s legal department decided that it was too much of a risk & feared a lawsuit.
it is not defamation or libelous to name the person who’s harmed you & to specifically name just what that harm was.

this is not an attack. 
this is not a threat.
this is not an attempt to degrade him.
this is not an attempt to shame him.

i am naming him to release myself from the three years of silence, trauma & fear i’ve had to endure.
i am naming him to free myself.

this is for all the girls & women who are still bound by silence, oppression & fear. 
this is for us. 
this is for our liberation.

text:
journey through your energetic being for self discovery and empowerment {plus; tools and techniques for self care}. whether it’s work, daily stress, interpersonal relationships, or everything that’s happening in the world today, we’ve all experienced difficult times. but what does that look like within you? what can we do in those moments, and what is available to us? in this workshop you’ll be diving into your energetic being and seeing what your energy centers represent in daily life. learning how being in and out of balance affects you. and learning different techniques, and tools for those areas. a day of exploration, grounding, centering, and coming back into balance.

rsvp to nyn@vashondoveproject.org or call (206) 940-6430 to find out more or to register.

this workshop is intended for victims and survivors of domestic violence, sexual assault, and those islanders who identify as #metoo. #selfcare
name: The DOVE Project
tweet_full:
journey through your energetic being for self discovery and empowerment {plus; tools and techniques for self care}. whether it’s work, daily stress, interpersonal relationships, or everything that’s happening in the world today, we’ve all experienced difficult times. but what does that look like within you? what can we do in those moments, and what is available to us? in this workshop you’ll be diving into your energetic being and seeing what your energy centers represent in daily life. learning how being in and out of balance affects you. and learning different techniques, and tools for those areas. a day of exploration, grounding, centering, and coming back into balance.

rsvp to nyn@vashondoveproject.org or call (206) 940-6430 to find out more or to register.

this workshop is intended for victims and survivors of domestic violence, sexual assault, and those islanders who identify as #metoo. #selfcare

text:
témoignage #1 : "tu étais mon ami. tu es venu chez moi après les cours pour que l'on mange ensemble. 
nous nous sommes rapprochés, puis nous avons finis par nous embrasser.
puis je ne sais pas ce qu'il t'a pris. tu m'as portée et tu m'as plaquée sur mon lit. tu m'as tenue les mains et le visage. tu t'es allongé sur moi, et tu as fait des mouvements de va-et-vient au dessus de mon jean. je pleurais, mais je ne sais pas si tu l'as vu. tu me faisais mal.
puis au bout d'un moment qui m'a semblé une éternité, tu t'es allongé à côté de moi. puis tu es parti. 
oui, j'ai eu honte. oui, j'ai pensé que c'était de ma faute. de t'avoir laissé venir chez moi, de t'avoir embrassé, et surtout de ne pas t'avoir repoussé. d'être restée paralysée et de ne rien avoir dit.
je pense que toi, tu n'as aucune idée de ce que tu as fait, mais depuis un an, ce moment me hante sans arrêt." #temoignage #dessin #drawing #pencil #sexualassault #metoo #feminism #equality #freedom #fight

pure jojoba beats your age
jojoba oil is rich in vitamin e. it plays the role of an antioxidant and strengthens the capillary walls in your skin. it acts as a natural anti-aging nutrient by improving the moisture and elasticity of the skin cells. studies found that vitamin e reduces inflammation helping to maintain a healthy and youthful appearance. the antioxidant properties help you against cigarette smoke or ultraviolet rays from sunlight, protecting against skin cancer. more info in bio link.
.

text_retweet:
@regran_ed from @belinda_vegan -  meet the victims of your "choices"... milk, cheese, ice cream, etc.
_
repost from @sosanimalscall  @theoccultussoulband
_
the dairy industry heavy marketed themselves for profit, such as the “got milk?” commercials.
.
“got milk” was actually an advertising campaign to encourage the consumption of milk, created by an advertising agency for the california milk processor board in 1993, and was later licensed for use by milk processors and dairy farmers.
.
the truth was hidden from us. and over time those who profited from exploiting animals, conditioned us.
.
maybe we were victims of the dairy industry ourselves, but we can no longer be complicit.
.
be #strong enough to seek the #truth, because the truth is out there. it will be through your own eyes, your own truth, in which you will find your own way to break out of that mold.
.
🌱 cruelty free, vegan alternatives: http://chooseveg.com/blog/choose-best-vegan-milk/
.

.

text:
"i was going to die, sooner or later, whether or not i had even spoken myself. my silences had not protected me. your silences will not protect you.... what are the words you do not yet have? what are the tyrannies you swallow day by day and attempt to make your own, until you will sicken and die of them, still in silence? we have been socialized to respect fear more than our own need for language."
.
i began to ask each time: "what's the worst that could happen to me if i tell this truth?" unlike women in other countries, our breaking silence is unlikely to have us jailed, "disappeared" or run off the road at night. our speaking out will irritate some people, get us called bitchy or hypersensitive and disrupt some dinner parties. and then our speaking out will permit other women to speak, until laws are changed and lives are saved and the world is altered forever.
.
next time, ask: what's the worst that will happen? then push yourself a little further than you dare. once you start to speak, people will yell at you. they will interrupt you, put you down and suggest it's personal. and the world won't end.
.
and the speaking will get easier and easier. and you will find you have fallen in love with your own vision, which you may never have realized you had. and you will lose some friends and lovers, and realize you don't miss them. and new ones will find you and cherish you. and you will still flirt and paint your nails, dress up and party, because, as i think emma goldman said, "if i can't dance, i don't want to be part of your revolution." and at last you'll know with surpassing certainty that only one thing is more frightening than speaking your truth. and that is not speaking."
.
- audre lorde
#metoo #womensempowerment #sexualassault #feminist #feminism #movement

text:
| [don't] look at me | © marinka masséus photography 2018
•
•
project reflecting on a woman's wish to be seen and her simultaneous impulse to hide herself, after centuries of misogynistic programming.

for centuries, women have been reduced solely to their appearance, their physical beauty deemed their only worth. western philosophers who have shaped our collective thinking - aristotle[i], socrates[ii], jean-jacques rousseau[iii], darwin[iv], schopenhauer[v], nietzsche[vi] - compared women to animals, incapable of rational thought, devoid of intelligence. and although present generations are desperately trying to escape these narrow confinements, the ingrained programming leaves many women struggling with their self-worth.

the objectification of the female body is an effective form of dehumanization. women's sexuality is exploited and suppressed at the same time. admired and reviled, chased and judged, praised and ridiculed, all at the same time. this opppresive societal schizophrenia is mirrored in every woman's soul.

this series reflects on the desire to be seen, coupled with the shame and instinctive need to hide.

text:
this is something that i’ve had a hard time sitting with. after years of pain, countless doc visits, one protocol after another.. i have some answers. i am doing the work. every. single. day.
•
i still find myself wanting immediate gratification. but this is where the growth happens. this is where we learn how strong we really are and how worthy we are even when we feel broken. we learn priorities. we learn boundaries. we really learn how to say no.
•
my new practice is sitting with this. putting my health above all. taking it moment by moment. not setting myself up for failure. and mostly just being intuitive with it.
•
how are you taking the time to heal? 💚

text:
it's natural to eat dogs.

everyone eats dogs.

people have been eating dogs since the beginning of time.

the dogs are humanely slaughtered.

dogs are not as smart as us.

dogs would go extinct is we didn't harvest them.

dogs taste good.

it's part of the food chain.

plants feel pain too.

these dog farmers treat their animals like family.

it's the circle of life.

you're never gonna stop people from eating dogs.

you're forcing your beliefs on us.

eating dogs is our tradition.

text:
“almost always, the creative dedicated minority has made the world better.” martin luther king 🙌
-

it was summer of 2015. my daughter started snapping some pictures of me, encouraging me to get back to the land of the living. .

she said, “mom, you should start an instagram account.” puzzled, i said, “what’s instagram?” my entry into the world of social media was a rapid one as she helped me set up an account, taught me how to do a caption and patiently explained to her 54 year old mother what a hashtag was. .

it’s hard to believe that just over 3 years later, i’m on a plane heading to meet @jamesnord and join the very first fohr freshman class at 57 years young. .

it’s an overwhelming feeling to know that just a few years ago, i knew absolutely no one in this world of social media. i knew nothing about technology. i had absolutely no clue how to do any of this. i wasn’t a model. i had no idea how to launch a blog. it happened organically as i began sharing my story in a very real and vulnerable way. people began reaching out and asking for help. i sent my cell phone to hundreds of people and simply listened and shared my story with them. .

as i began to find my voice and help others, i began finding my way back to me. i began to develop confidence for the first time in my life. as a #metoo at a young age, i lost my voice. i lost all sense of who i was and it would take me a lifetime to find out who i was. .

i couldn’t be more honored to join @fohr to represent the underrepresented. my mission to use my voice and to launch an international movement, the forever fierce revolution, happened organically by helping one person at a time. .

it’s funny that we don’t really talk about ageism yet it’s the only “ism” we all share. it’s the only form of discrimination that every single person will ultimately face if they are lucky enough to reach midlife. .

i’m lucky. lucky to have reached midlife. lucky to have survived a life threatening illness that changed me so deeply and set me on a course to change the world and the way we view older women. .

dreams really do come true if only you believe...believe in you. thank you to @fohr💗
name: ✨Catherine Grace O'Connell✨

text:
😄💕👧🏾🌈today's affirmation: "out of self-respect, i surround myself with loving and kind people." | if you find yourself in the midst of an energetic warfare with your environment and/or those in it, it's important to remember that a big part of your self-care routine includes other people. this is especially true if you are called to be a healer. often, we attract people who are living in a state of unawareness, searching outside of themselves for the wholeness that can only come from within. so, they project their fears, confusion, doubts, and insecurities onto others to protect themselves from accepting the consequences of self-responsibility. 💯don't take it personally, your purpose is bigger than you. but to walk in it powerfully, you more than a positive mindset. you need the love and support of other people.

where can you go to connect with loving and kind people who will encourage, inspire and affirm you? 
where can you link up with kindred spirits who will partner in your success even if that means cheering you along and holding you accountable to your dreams every step of the way? 💎check out meetup.com, civic groups in your area, a facebook group such as the women's healing circle (click link in bio to join @rohiniwellness or visit bit.ly/iamsacredbeauty), a nearby spiritual center, a yoga studio, a local psychic fair or metaphysical shop, a fitness group or gym, volunteer at a community-based organization... there are so many places to connect with people whom you vibe with so that you can share, feel restored, inspired, and supported.

ignore the haters who can't yet see far enough past their own trauma to show up in a way that is healthy and supportive.

you deserve community, love, intimacy, laughter, respect, fun, support, encouragement, partnership...the wonderful company of people with whom you can truly let your hair down!

don't wait for the 'right people' to show up in your life. go out and look for your tribe, you'll find them faster than you thought possible! 
if you'd like further suggestions, send me a dm.

in peace & beauty,
🌻dominique

p.s. join the women's healing circle at @rohiniwellness or visit bit.ly/iamsacredbeauty

text:
it's natural to eat turkeys.

everyone eats turkeys.

people have been eating turkeys since the beginning of time.

the turkeys are humanely slaughtered.

turkeys are not as smart as us.

turkeys would go extinct is we didn't harvest them.

text:
k i d s 
what do we think of children, and their role in the world? are they mini versions of us? tiny wannabe adults? to be seen and not heard? when you really think about it, it’s hard to answer isn’t it?
______
many of us want to be able to see our children as the unique individuals they are, but it often seems that we’re really up against it because the society that surrounds us is so child-ist. childism is defined as "a prejudice against children on the ground of a belief that they are property and can (or even should) be controlled, enslaved, or removed to serve adult needs." ________
you’d be hard pressed to find someone who agrees with the latter part of that sentence... but control? controlling our children is something that is honoured in our society. baby crying? it’s not unusual to get a bit of side eye. toddler screaming? people generally look on in disapproval with maybe a few audible tuts. child refuses to give a hug to a perfect stranger? how rude. 
________
nowadays we’re in a strange space. we spend time telling adults it’s ok to express their difficult emotions, while telling children it’s not ok for them to express theirs. instead, frequently, children are shamed for expressing their undeveloped feelings in an undeveloped way. and we feel shamed too, because that expression of emotion is somehow our fault, and it’s our fault it’s inconveniencing those around us.
__________
imagine a world where children were, maybe not central, but as valued as adults. where public spaces all had play areas and people offered you help instead of judgment. and to the dad in the airport who soothed a screaming toddler while an entire departure lounge looked on shaking their heads- you’re amazing. and to all of you who fight that same fight every day, you’re amazing too. it doesn’t seem like a big deal, but those daily battles against societal standards, feeling those glares while you try your best to calm your uncalmable child- they all add up to a huge difference for the next generation. 
__________
if you’d like to read more on childism, take a look at the work of elisabeth young-breuhl and robin grille.

text:
i realize that the judicial systems need evidence to believe children when they come forward about being sexually abused. but sexual perpetrators are very astute when it comes to hiding the evidence that would incriminate them to the criminal offense. in my case, physical and sexual abuse was indisputable because i had severe burn marks inside my private parts. my father would torture me whenever i would hide or fight him off and he would punish me by burning me. my father knew very well how to conceal his physical abuse and sexual abuse. but physical force or violence are rarely used, rather the perpetrator tries to manipulate the child’s trust and hide the sexual abuse. in many cases there isn’t enough evidence to present to the police to substantiate the crime either because it was fondling, masturbation, forcing the minor to masturbate or oral copulation. it is very hard to prove these cases in our judicial system. also, minors that are sexually abused by female perpetrators are unable to present substantial “evidence” to conclude that they were in fact sexually abused. even in legally confirmed cases of sexual abuse, most children do not have physical findings diagnostic of sexual abuse. therefore, the child's disclosure is often the most important piece of information in determining the likelihood of sexual abuse. we must listen to and believe children because requiring a sexual abuse allegation to be “proven” with “evidence” in a court of law is an impossibly high bar that perpetuates impunity for sexual predators.

text: every 6 months i update my curriculum vita and linkedin to check in with myself what i have learned and accomplished in that period. every monday i set weekly goals that i review the following monday. these goals are categorized as writing (what did i write this week?), reading (what did i read this week?), learning (what new things did i learn this week?), doing good (what did i do that had a positive impact on someone else?), and me time (what did i do for myself to feel better?) my goal is to have ✅ in all my categories every week. some weeks are better than others but i never stop pushing myself. there is no better rival than you.

text: ब्रेक के बाद बॉलीवुड में फिर #metoo अभियान शुरू हो गया है. पहले से ही बीमारियों से परेशान ब्रेक के बाद इसके पहले शिकार नवाजुद्दीन बने हैं. इसके पहले #metoo के तेज से कई अभिनेता, निर्माता, निर्देशक, पत्रकार और राजनेता झुलस चुके हैं. इसी के कारण मोदी सरकार के राज्य मंत्री रहे एमजे अकबर को इस्तीफा देना पड़ा था. उनका मुकदमा चल रहा है. अब इस सूची में बॉलीवुड के मशहूर सितारे ‘नवज़ुद्दीन सिद्दीकी’ का नाम भी शामिल हो गया है. अभिनेत्री निहारिका सिंह ने नवाज़ पर यौन उत्पीड़न का आरोप लगाया है. आरोप के अनुसार निहारिका के बार-बार मना करने के बावजूद नवाज़ उनके साथ शारीरिक संबंध रखना चाहते थे. जारी किए एक पोस्ट में निहारिका लिखती हैं “मैंने उन्हे अपने आपसे दूर रखने की बहुत कोशिश की, पर वो मानने को तैयार ही नहीं थे. काफी नाकामयाब कोशिशों के बाद मैंने आखिर में हार मन ली. #bollywood #follow #likeforlikes #love #india #hollywood #fashion #art #instagram #actor #mumbai #dubai #bhfyp #art #love #india #follow #hollywood #salmankhan #fashion #instagood #hot #instagram #actor #mumbai #dubai
name: Nationalwheels India News

stop_filter_tweet: ब्रेक के बाद बॉलीवुड में फिर अभियान शुरू हो गया है . पहले से ही बीमारियों से परेशान ब्रेक के बाद इसके पहले शिकार नवाजुद्दीन बने हैं . इसके पहले के तेज से कई अभिनेता , निर्माता , निर्देशक , पत्रकार और राजनेता झुलस चुके हैं . इसी के कारण मोदी सरकार के राज्य मंत्री रहे एमजे अकबर को इस्तीफा देना पड़ा था . उनका मुकदमा चल रहा है . अब इस सूची में बॉलीवुड के मशहूर सितारे ‘ नवज़ुद्दीन सिद्दीकी ’ का नाम भी शामिल हो गया है . अभिनेत्री निहारिका सिंह ने नवाज़ पर यौन उत्पीड़न का आरोप लगाया है . आरोप के अनुसार निहारिका के बार-बार मना करने के बावजूद नवाज़ उनके साथ शारीरिक संबंध रखना चाहते थे . जारी किए एक पोस्ट में निहारिका लिखती हैं “ मैंने उन्हे अपने आपसे दूर रखने की बहुत कोशिश की , पर वो मानने को तैयार ही नहीं थे . काफी नाकामयाब कोशिशों के बाद मैंने आखिर में हार मन ली .

text: alex is right! glad he has joined the movement! for those who say ‘just don’t rape/sexually harass anyone and you have nothing to worry about’... well in this ‘just believe women’ witch hunt mindset where an allegation without evidence can cost someone a job, sponsorships, reputation etc. it has become very dangerous even if you did nothing wrong. like the aziz ansari situation there can be an honest misunderstanding and as with countless situations where a college athlete about to go pro dumps his girlfriend she can make up a total lie with malicious intent to get revenge. i have been falsely accused in my life twice so i have first experience that women can lie. men shouldn’t have to walk on egg shells around women for fear the wrong compliment might lead to a me too accusation now the world is looking at you crazy like ‘i wonder if he did it?’ not cool! this is not to discredit the real victims of assault or to defend monsters like weinstein or spacey or ratner or cosby etc. the me too movement was much needed and gave many women a voice but sadly some (not all) women are using this movement for evil. which makes it harder for women who really have been assaulted believed. men must protect ourselves from these women. no one is asking for people to say ‘aw poor men they have it so hard’ or that this concern equals what women go through but it is a concern we should be aware of and not afraid to voice or bring attention to. think if your brothers sons husbands boyfriends etc... #metoo

text:
yes yes, it’s another #mayurasana . but today it’s with a little message i feel i need to share. this morning i included #mayurasana in the class i was teaching. i thought the class was doing pretty well, but a couple of ladies were struggling. obviously, i gave them hints and tips as best as i could. until one of the ladies said “it just feels like my boobs are in the way”. only then did i realise that for some women, that poses a challenge. but because she told me, we were able to find a way around that. .

my point is that i was really glad she told me this. it was an honest and very helpful remark she made. yes, it included the word #boob. and yes, we had to discuss #boobs and and how to work around them. but it was all in a very respectful manner. .

lately there’s been so much to do about #metoo that a lot of men (including me) are unsure on what’s appropriate and what isn’t. and today i’ve come to conclude that it’s the intention that counts. because it was perfectly ok to discuss her boobs because our intention was to get her into the posture. it would have been very not ok, to grab her by the boobs because that would have had a completely different intention. i think… wow, and all this because of one lady discussing her boobs in my yoga class. i wonder what we’ll discuss next week…
name: Daniel
tweet_full:
yes yes, it’s another #mayurasana . but today it’s with a little message i feel i need to share. this morning i included #mayurasana in the class i was teaching. i thought the class was doing pretty well, but a couple of ladies were struggling. obviously, i gave them hints and tips as best as i could. until one of the ladies said “it just feels like my boobs are in the way”. only then did i realise that for some women, that poses a challenge. but because she told me, we were able to find a way around that. .

my point is that i was really glad she told me this. it was an honest and very helpful remark she made. yes, it included the word #boob. and yes, we had to discuss #boobs and and how to work around them. but it was all in a very respectful manner. .

lately there’s been so much to do about #metoo that a lot of men (including me) are unsure on what’s appropriate and what isn’t. and today i’ve come to conclude that it’s the intention that counts. because it was perfectly ok to discuss her boobs because our intention was to get her into the posture. it would have been very not ok, to grab her by the boobs because that would have had a completely different intention. i think… wow, and all this because of one lady discussing her boobs in my yoga class. i wonder what we’ll discuss next week…

text:
super proud to share that a week ago the @thelilynews installed a mural designed by our @boglio_boglio at @thelinehotel in dc! it was live-painted over the course of election night and depicts an eagle with feathers representing the 184 female candidates who were not incumbents on the ballot in congressional and gubernatorial races throughout the country. each time a female candidate won her seat, a feather was painted purple. major thanks to our friends @spectrummurals for painting, the @thelinehotel for the space, & @thelilynews / @washingtonpost in partnership with @tresemme. 🖤

super proud to share that a week ago the @thelilynews installed a mural designed by our @boglio_boglio at @thelinehotel in dc! it was live-painted over the course of election night and depicts an eagle with feathers representing the 184 female candidates who were not incumbents on the ballot in congressional and gubernatorial races throughout the country. each time a female candidate won her seat, a feather was painted purple. major thanks to our friends @spectrummurals for painting, the @thelinehotel for the space, & @thelilynews / @washingtonpost in partnership with @tresemme. 🖤
